This is a converted map directly from the game Counter Strike 1.6 from Counter Strike Source. I redid all the textures, I think that for the arena it is quite good. If you want to use my map in yours, please ask permission. Since the map had some lighting problems, I added special brushes that block the light, because even through the closed brushes you can still see the light at the edges. Instead of the standard textures, I made the developer's textures, so that the map weighs very little, but is good to play and does not lag. Immediately upon spawning, each player will have 35 hep.

I decided to remake this map a little bit, as I was very much reminded of the time when I played this map back in Counter-Strike 1.6, when the two teams ran to each other with the words "It's time to die!" and started mass-cutting with each other

A small Dev Texture level which is great for very short and intense rounds. Sight-lines are long so be careful and don't get sniped!

_sText:
My first Counter-Strike map, bringing my vision of merging 1.6 and CSS's Assault together.  
The goal were simplifying/tidy up the environment and get rid of the hostage rescue mode. I like the fast paced gameplay the original Assault has but it has lots of problems that hinder the fun. Source's remake were beautiful but the place were clutter with prop and I miss the night lighting 1.6 has, so v1622 is a little bit of both with the bomb defuse twist.  

The map support up to 32 players (16 each). Has overview/radar and nav mesh.
Happy christmas and New Year

_sText:
This map is a centric (literal) map that uses a mix of orange and gray dev_measure textures.

AWPs can be found outside behind cover, this was done as a way to prevent people from being shot as soon as they step out of spawn. Additionally, there is also AWPs in the tunnel network below, and can be found right through the hole in the middle of every spawn.

There is no buy zones, as this is intended to be strictly played with AWPs, however, if you wish to try out other weapons you are still able to give yourself some through the console.
- sv_cheats 1
- give weapon_[name]

Whole changelis compared to V5 is here:
• Map is in xmas textures, xmas props added too, songs are replaced by Xmas songs, thy now play in 3 rooms and exterior too, thanx to installed speakers :P
• Teleport room is now textured and there is light too, there is also trigger_hurt to avoid CTS camp there. Now there is prop block too, so you cant barricade there.
• Elevator is now uglitchable by guns, gun block added.
• Tons of new Skip/Hints/areaportals added, its much lighter for CPU/GPU
• New spawnpoint added, Its whole new place, with new connection between "this is not room" and "broken elevator"
• New entrances to disco added: 1st Door in pipeline corridor, 2nd One time usable teleport on CT Ramp and 3th T ramp, 4th is in new teleport room
• New Teleport room next to broken elevator.
• CT ramp is little lowered and fence is deleted
• Added 64box into room1 for zombies
• Added new camp in exterior (rust watertank)
• Added new entrances for roof on Disco place
• Added new teleport in teleport room,
• Added new secretvent with teleport in new Spawnplace
• Teleport rooms and some other secret holes are now marked/flagged by Xmas stickers. So they are now easy to find :P
• Xmas lights everywhere, so there is still light when all lights are turned off
• Smoke added on chimney in exterior :D
• Fire place added for better xmas ambience

​• Small props added in "this is not room" for zombies to easier climb up
​• Invisible ladder added in secret breakable entrance between staircase and red ventcorridor
​• CT vent entrance is now 64units big, that means its now walkable, no need for crough
​• Many prop blocks added, to avoid unfair barricades
​• Map has more light, so its not dark
​​• There are more changes, but Ive already forgot about them lol
